title: Sept: First month in 6 years no NFL players arrested
text:
Sept: First month in 6 years no NFL players arrested Mike Foss, USA Today 10:20 a.m. CDT October 2, 2015 Green Bay Packers' Sean Richardson breaks up a pass intended for New Orleans Saints' Keenan Lewis during the second half of an NFL preseason football game Thursday, Sept. 3, 2015, in Green Bay, Wis. (AP Photo/Jeffrey Phelps) (Photo: AP) 
The 2015 NFL season has started well enough. Tom Brady is playing out of his mind. So is Aaron Rodgers. There has been drama and parity. There have been some controversies, banter, and a blossoming friendship with the Saved by the Bell cast. 
No one has been arrested in a while either. In fact, the NFL just managed to go a full calendar month without an arrest for the first time in six years according to Mike Rosenberg of the San Jose Mercury News. NFL just finished a calendar month without any player arrests reported. That hadn't happened in more than 6 years. — Mike Rosenberg (@RosenbergMerc) October 1, 2015 
So even though the NFL is calling a record number of penalties off the field in 2015, players are staying out of trouble off it – at least for September. It’s a safe bet that Cris Carter probably has a theory for this trend of good behavior.
